snippet.textDisplay: That speed sticker is a german thing. First up ;-) you can see it has M+S printed on it which means "Matsch und Schnee" (mud and snow) and second this is law in Germany. You HAVE to apply these if the tires are lower speed than the car can do. People do it all the time here because usually slower tires are much cheaper.
